President Cyril Ramaphosa will on Tuesday receive Letters of Credence from Heads of Mission-Designate at a Credentials Ceremony at Sefako Makgatho Presidential Guesthouse in Pretoria. “The President will welcome 18 Heads of Mission-Designate, who have arrived in South Africa to serve in diplomatic missions,” the Presidency said in a statement.   Heads of Mission-Designate from the following countries will serve in South Africa, with the aim of advancing diplomatic relations: Members of the public can follow proceedings of the Credentials Ceremony on Presidency and government digital platforms from 15:00. – SAnews.gov.za